Description: Fragment of a seal-impression, the fine brown Nile clay has some mica inclusions and was hardened after excavation. The rear shows a small area of what might be wood impression, left and right of it turned string impressions with a width of 0.15 cm. The top bears an oval scarab-like seal-impression with a circumferential line. Two signs preserved that are not clearly recognisable, parts of an animal (?back of lion) and a second sign that mirrors the curved end of the seal.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
